1
00:00:00,430 --> 00:00:03,760
<i>The girl you hurt... Was it Ama?</i>

2
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:05,540
<i>Why did you lie to me?</i>

3
00:00:05,540 --> 00:00:08,420
<i>There's no way
I wouldn't know who Kairi is.</i>

4
00:00:08,420 --> 00:00:09,550
I'm so sorry.

5
00:00:09,550 --> 00:00:12,770
Chiaki, stop, please.

6
00:00:16,170 --> 00:00:21,970
I should have done this sooner,
to make you mine alone.

7
00:00:25,070 --> 00:00:29,370
No, please, stop...

8
00:00:30,630 --> 00:00:33,130
Please... No!

9
00:00:33,130 --> 00:00:34,830
Stop.

10
00:00:36,980 --> 00:00:39,700
It's your fault for lying, Ama.

11
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:43,960
No.

12
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,990
Please, stop it.

13
00:00:51,770 --> 00:00:53,970
Now, finally.

14
00:01:05,884 --> 00:01:07,287
I'm sorry.

15
00:01:07,938 --> 00:01:09,278
I...

16
00:01:10,412 --> 00:01:12,392
I didn't mean to...

17
00:01:25,030 --> 00:01:26,450
I'm sorry.

18
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:31,510
I love you.

19
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:37,810
I really do love you, Ama.

20
00:01:38,630 --> 00:01:40,590
I'm going crazy over you.

21
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:57,850
I'm going home.

22
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,080
Ama?

23
00:02:02,450 --> 00:02:04,170
Wait!

24
00:02:07,860 --> 00:02:11,710
I'm sorry I lied.

25
00:02:14,060 --> 00:02:17,240
I didn't do anything bad with him.

26
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:23,890
I just didn't want to make you feel uneasy.

27
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:29,030
I should have been honest.

28
00:02:31,650 --> 00:02:33,080
But...

29
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:41,400
was it bad enough...

30
00:02:42,390 --> 00:02:44,490
for you to do this?

31
00:02:47,270 --> 00:02:49,410
I'm truly sorry.

32
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:52,870
- I was...
- I want to keep some distance.

33
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:56,600
I won't contact you for a while.

34
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:03,530
No, Ama.

35
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,550
I'm sorry.

36
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,140
I won't do it again.

37
00:03:12,020 --> 00:03:13,680
Please.

38
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:17,620
Don't go.

39
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,790
Ama...

40
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,090
Ama.

41
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:39,680
Kairi-senpai, good morning.

42
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,030
Morning.

43
00:04:41,630 --> 00:04:44,700
Is your injury okay?

44
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:47,030
Yeah, it's nothing.

45
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:49,620
So,

46
00:04:50,410 --> 00:04:53,220
Chiaki was the boyfriend all along.

47
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:54,970
Yes.

48
00:04:55,810 --> 00:04:57,940
We've been close since way back.

49
00:04:57,940 --> 00:05:00,070
We hung out a lot.

50
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:01,160
I see.

51
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:03,180
When did it end yesterday?

52
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:07,690
That was crazy yesterday.

53
00:05:07,690 --> 00:05:11,600
So, does that mean
Ms. Minase is involved with both of them?

54
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,640
Right?

55
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,320
I didn't expect that from her.

56
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:16,040
Oh, man.

57
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,700
But she's cute, so it's okay.

58
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,940
No, you should keep that off set.

59
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:21,760
That's true.

60
00:05:22,610 --> 00:05:27,220
Yeah, but it's cool knowing
what's going on behind the scenes.

61
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:28,710
Hey!

62
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:33,340
Would you stop with those rumors?

63
00:05:33,340 --> 00:05:35,170
I'm sorry!

64
00:05:38,491 --> 00:05:40,330
That felt good.

65
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:46,540
Ama.

66
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:49,090
Don't worry about them.

67
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:52,930
I'm sorry for causing trouble.

68
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:54,960
Thanks, Rin.

69
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:59,280
Well, let's shake it off
and do our best on set today.

70
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,770
Okay.

71
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:02,700
Alright, let's go.

72
00:06:08,869 --> 00:06:11,849
[Mr. Chiaki]

73
00:06:13,860 --> 00:06:15,349
[Mr. Chiaki]

74
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:21,120
Ama?

75
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,040
Sorry.

76
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:30,340
<i>The number you dialed
is either out of range, or turned off.</i>

77
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:34,140
<i>The number you dialed
is either out of range...</i>

78
00:06:57,780 --> 00:07:00,380
- Good work today.
- Good work.

79
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:06,640
Ama!

80
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:13,510
Saotome.

81
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:17,350
Disappear!
Disappear, disappear, disappear!

82
00:07:17,350 --> 00:07:18,990
What do you want?

83
00:07:18,990 --> 00:07:22,400
Geez, you don't have to be so guarded.

84
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:26,360
Oh, by the way,
that must have been rough on you.

85
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:32,000
Mr. Hosho punched Mr. Asakura, right?

86
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:38,830
I just happened to hear about it. That's all.

87
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:41,990
And I'd heard bad rumors about Mr. Hosho,

88
00:07:41,990 --> 00:07:46,410
so I've been worried about you, Ama.

89
00:07:46,410 --> 00:07:48,560
Bad rumors?

90
00:07:50,890 --> 00:07:54,910
That he toys with girls
and then throws them away.

91
00:07:54,910 --> 00:07:58,240
Chiaki is not that kind of person.

92
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,000
Don't say such baseless things.

93
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,730
Want me to introduce you?

94
00:08:02,730 --> 00:08:06,240
To a girl who was hurt by Chiaki Hosho.

95
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,830
Ama, this is Hibiki.

96
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:15,360
Hey, Chiaki.

97
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:17,790
I don't want to break up.

98
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:23,050
Ama wants to know about Chiaki Hosho.

99
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:24,469
I don't really...

100
00:08:24,469 --> 00:08:26,460
Don't be fooled.

101
00:08:26,460 --> 00:08:27,460
Huh?

102
00:08:27,460 --> 00:08:29,760
That guy is a scumbag.

103
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:36,425
I got close to Chiaki
after we worked together.

104
00:08:37,170 --> 00:08:41,390
He asked me out to dinner,
and I fell for him.

105
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:46,660
It didn't take long
for us to become intimate.

106
00:08:47,710 --> 00:08:49,190
But,

107
00:08:49,190 --> 00:08:53,080
once I got serious,
his attitude changed completely.

108
00:08:54,830 --> 00:08:58,180
Are you sure
you want me to spread that video?

109
00:08:58,180 --> 00:08:59,400
Huh?

110
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:03,670
You were making quite the noise.

111
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:07,750
If that gets out,

112
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:11,100
you'll have to leave the industry.

113
00:09:14,350 --> 00:09:17,850
What? Hibiki, I'm so sorry!

114
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:20,820
That Chiaki Hosho is a jerk!

115
00:09:20,820 --> 00:09:22,280
He's the worst!

116
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,410
No way!

117
00:09:23,410 --> 00:09:24,650
Chiaki would never...

118
00:09:24,650 --> 00:09:26,820
Here's a photo of us.

119
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:46,960
Chiaki, are you okay?

120
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:49,930
I heard you bailed on work.

121
00:09:54,730 --> 00:09:57,190
Things not going well with her?

122
00:09:58,240 --> 00:09:59,910
Maybe...

123
00:10:01,150 --> 00:10:02,990
I should die.

124
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:04,680
Huh?

125
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:07,834
Don't say that, even as a joke.

126
00:10:07,834 --> 00:10:09,414
Drink some water.

127
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:13,490
I don't feel alive.

128
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:15,580
Huh?

129
00:10:17,780 --> 00:10:20,530
I'm nervous not having Ama around.

130
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:25,790
I feel like I'm going crazy.

131
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:28,870
I love her so much, I can't help myself.

132
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,800
Honestly,

133
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:35,210
I want to snatch her up right now,
and keep her locked up next to me.

134
00:10:35,210 --> 00:10:39,420
I want to ruin her
so she can't live without me.

135
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,800
If Ama ever belongs to anyone but me...

136
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:51,780
I want to die with her.

137
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:01,030
In the end...

138
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:05,960
this is the only way I know how to live.

139
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:20,390
Ready? Action!

140
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:24,820
Yu, you really are like that sometimes.

141
00:11:24,820 --> 00:11:26,210
That's not true.

142
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:28,110
It's just that I...

143
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:31,170
Cut!

144
00:11:31,170 --> 00:11:32,360
Are you okay?

145
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,760
Not feeling well?

146
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,300
I'm sorry.

147
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,450
Let's take a short break.

148
00:11:38,220 --> 00:11:40,110
We'll resume in 15 minutes!

149
00:11:40,110 --> 00:11:42,580
- 15 minutes.
- 15 minutes.

150
00:11:44,740 --> 00:11:45,970
<i>It's no good.</i>

151
00:11:45,970 --> 00:11:48,590
<i>I can't concentrate at all.</i>

152
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,830
Alright!

153
00:11:53,830 --> 00:11:56,130
Let's drink after we're done!

154
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:58,510
Ms. Rin.

155
00:11:58,510 --> 00:12:01,350
That includes you who's glancing over here!

156
00:12:08,970 --> 00:12:13,530
I'm sorry for stopping the shoot
so many times today.

157
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:18,080
Do you feel uncomfortable on set?

158
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:21,800
No, it's not that.

159
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:25,330
If anyone says anything weird,
let me know, okay?

160
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:27,690
I'll give them an earful.

161
00:12:27,690 --> 00:12:29,950
Thank you.

162
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:34,660
Anyway, let's drink, eat,
and forget about it all today!

163
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:41,520
Oh no.

164
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,260
It's from my manager.

165
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:47,460
I forgot I had a magazine interview.

166
00:12:47,460 --> 00:12:49,180
Seriously?

167
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:50,410
I'm so sorry!

168
00:12:50,410 --> 00:12:52,770
- See you later, Ama.
- Okay.

169
00:12:52,770 --> 00:12:55,470
Good grief. She's always in a rush.

170
00:12:55,470 --> 00:12:56,820
Yes.

171
00:13:07,850 --> 00:13:11,140
So how have things been?

172
00:13:11,140 --> 00:13:12,800
With Chiaki.

173
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:19,010
I haven't seen him, or contacted him.

174
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:22,890
I see.

175
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:29,360
Actually, what kind of person was he,
from your perspective?

176
00:13:30,730 --> 00:13:33,900
What do you mean by that?

177
00:13:36,070 --> 00:13:40,360
I'm starting to have trouble

178
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,990
understanding who Chiaki is.

179
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:48,720
Depending on the answer,

180
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:52,500
are you going to break up with him?

181
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,964
From what I know,

182
00:14:10,870 --> 00:14:13,900
he was a hopeless mess
when it came to women.

183
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:20,440
He'd target innocent-looking girls,
and take bets on them.

184
00:14:22,550 --> 00:14:28,300
There was even a bet on whether
he could get you within three months.

185
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:30,571
He suggested it.

186
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,670
What?

187
00:14:48,911 --> 00:14:52,091
Well, take care.

188
00:14:53,830 --> 00:14:55,440
Are you okay?

189
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:58,400
I'm fine.

190
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,450
See you on set.

191
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,540
Yeah.

192
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:21,902
[Mr. Chiaki]

193
00:15:31,150 --> 00:15:32,277
[Ama]

194
00:15:34,590 --> 00:15:36,270
Hello?

195
00:15:36,270 --> 00:15:37,840
Ama?

196
00:15:38,613 --> 00:15:43,000
<i>I'm sorry I haven't been replying.</i>

197
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:46,880
No, it's my fault.

198
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:51,920
I've been thinking a lot since then.

199
00:15:55,070 --> 00:15:57,170
I want to break up.

200
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:03,790
Huh?

201
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:07,430
Because I found out that the Chiaki I know

202
00:16:07,430 --> 00:16:10,310
was only a small part of him.

203
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:13,440
What do you mean?

204
00:16:16,470 --> 00:16:19,720
That you hurt girls without a second thought.

205
00:16:21,090 --> 00:16:24,320
You even bet on
whether you could get me, right?

206
00:16:25,850 --> 00:16:28,940
<i>I can't trust you anymore.</i>

207
00:16:31,810 --> 00:16:35,710
<i>Thank you for everything until now.</i>

208
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,260
I see.

209
00:17:39,662 --> 00:17:43,872
She found out about the real me.

210
00:17:46,330 --> 00:17:49,730
But I'll never let you go
until the day I die.

211
00:17:52,830 --> 00:17:54,550
I can't live...

212
00:17:55,620 --> 00:17:58,080
without you anymore.

213
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:10,263
I have to pull myself together.

214
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,810
I don't want to cause
any more trouble for everyone.

215
00:18:17,860 --> 00:18:19,180
Come in.

216
00:18:20,270 --> 00:18:23,360
Do you have a minute?

217
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,560
Yes.

218
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,320
Sorry to bother you.

219
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,670
It's fine.

220
00:18:30,670 --> 00:18:33,367
So, what did you want to talk about?

221
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:38,600
I feel like both of you

222
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:43,370
aren't quite becoming your characters.

223
00:18:43,370 --> 00:18:48,400
Yu and Kengo were lovers.

224
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:50,240
They end up breaking up,

225
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:53,580
but they loved each other deeply, right?

226
00:18:53,580 --> 00:18:57,710
That kind of aura...

227
00:18:58,810 --> 00:19:01,880
It isn't coming from you two.

228
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:02,980
I'm sorry.

229
00:19:02,980 --> 00:19:06,170
No, I'm not angry.

230
00:19:06,170 --> 00:19:09,141
I'm just wondering what we should do.

231
00:19:11,540 --> 00:19:16,650
For example, how about spending time together
off set?

232
00:19:16,650 --> 00:19:20,430
- Huh?
- Actually try acting like a couple.

233
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:25,830
That way, you might get a feel
for loving each other.

234
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:27,630
Wait...

235
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:30,320
That's...

236
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,490
I understand.

237
00:19:32,490 --> 00:19:35,430
I'll give it a try before the next shoot.

238
00:19:38,670 --> 00:19:40,590
What should we do?

239
00:19:40,590 --> 00:19:44,080
I guess we'd have a date or something?

240
00:19:45,961 --> 00:19:48,510
But outside, people might see us.

241
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:50,430
That's true.

242
00:19:50,430 --> 00:19:52,560
Then come to my place.

243
00:19:54,130 --> 00:19:55,469
No...

244
00:19:56,317 --> 00:19:57,560
That's not right.

245
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,390
Sorry.

246
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:02,010
You're a popular actor, after all.

247
00:20:02,010 --> 00:20:04,430
Going to your place is risky.

248
00:20:04,430 --> 00:20:06,047
Yeah.

249
00:20:07,270 --> 00:20:09,730
Oh, how about my place?

250
00:20:09,730 --> 00:20:13,780
My family is at a relative's house right now,
so no one's home.

251
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:16,650
Huh? Is that okay?

252
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,710
Of course!

253
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:20,310
Then let's go.

254
00:20:20,310 --> 00:20:21,780
Okay.

255
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:24,100
Alright!

256
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,010
Did you say something?

257
00:20:26,010 --> 00:20:27,940
No, nothing.

258
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,870
Hey.

259
00:20:43,050 --> 00:20:45,260
What do you want?

260
00:20:46,410 --> 00:20:49,410
I heard from Shiki.

261
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,630
Things aren't going well with her?

262
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:57,640
Shut up.

263
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:02,170
Chiaki, you hide it well,

264
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:05,600
but inside, you're still a kid.

265
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:17,510
Want me to tell you something good?

266
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,120
What?

267
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:40,510
I heard that Chiaki Hosho and Kairi Asakura

268
00:21:40,510 --> 00:21:45,880
got into a fistfight over a new actress.

269
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:51,050
Go verify it for me!

270
00:21:51,050 --> 00:21:55,100
Oh, I'll introduce you
to a staff member on set, okay?

271
00:22:26,290 --> 00:22:28,640
Why is Kairi here?

272
00:22:34,330 --> 00:22:38,460
It's a bit messy, but come in.

273
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,370
Thanks for having me.

274
00:23:09,330 --> 00:23:13,360
I really wish Kairi would just die.

275
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:18,558
Don't touch Ama, don't get near her.

276
00:23:19,503 --> 00:23:21,070
This is the worst.

277
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,980
Die.

278
00:23:22,980 --> 00:23:27,600
Die, die, die, die!

279
00:23:35,730 --> 00:23:37,970
Even now, I still love you.

280
00:23:37,970 --> 00:23:40,340
I'm in love with you, Ama.

281
